{"id":4528,"date":"2026-01-18T20:41:18","date_gmt":"2026-01-18T15:11:18","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/?page_id=4528"},"modified":"2026-01-18T20:45:37","modified_gmt":"2026-01-18T15:15:37","slug":"the-blueprint-of-experiences-in-bhakti-from-steady-practice-to-fully-ripened-love","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/seminars\/2025\/japan\/bhakti-lata-3\/","title":{"rendered":"The blueprint of experiences\u00a0in\u00a0bhakti\u00a0from steady\u00a0practice to\u00a0fully\u00a0ripened\u00a0love!\u00a0"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<iframe title=\"Bhakti Lata (Part 3) by HH Bhanu Swami Maharaj on 13 Nov 2025\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/HLAAi902Vtg?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen><\/iframe>\n<\/div><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Bhakti Lata&nbsp;\u2013&nbsp;3&nbsp;| HH Bhanu Swami Maharaj | ISKCON Japan |&nbsp;13 Nov 2025<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">jaya&nbsp;r\u0101dh\u0101-m\u0101dhava&nbsp;ku\u00f1ja-vih\u0101r\u012b&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">gop\u012bjana-vallabha&nbsp;giri-vara-dh\u0101r\u012b&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">ya\u015bod\u0101-nandana&nbsp;vraja-jana-ra\u00f1jana&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">yamun\u0101-t\u012bra-vana-c\u0101r\u012b&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">Hare&nbsp;K\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a&nbsp;Hare&nbsp;K\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a&nbsp;K\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a&nbsp;K\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a&nbsp;Hare&nbsp;Hare&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">Hare R\u0101ma Hare R\u0101ma&nbsp;R\u0101ma&nbsp;R\u0101ma&nbsp;Hare&nbsp;Hare&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">Jaya&nbsp;Prabhup\u0101da&nbsp;Jaya&nbsp;Prabhup\u0101da&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">Prabhup\u0101da&nbsp;Jaya&nbsp;Prabhup\u0101da&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">&nbsp;<br>nama&nbsp;o\u1e41&nbsp;vi\u1e63\u1e47u-p\u0101d\u0101ya&nbsp;k\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a-pre\u1e63\u1e6dh\u0101ya&nbsp;bh\u016b-tale&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">\u015br\u012bmate&nbsp;bhaktived\u0101nta-sv\u0101min&nbsp;iti&nbsp;n\u0101mine&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">namas&nbsp;te&nbsp;s\u0101rasvate&nbsp;deve&nbsp;gaura-v\u0101\u1e47\u012b-prac\u0101ri\u1e47e&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">nirvi\u015be\u1e63a-\u015b\u016bnyav\u0101di-p\u0101\u015bc\u0101tya-de\u015ba-t\u0101ri\u1e47e&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">jaya&nbsp;\u015br\u012b-k\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a-caitanya&nbsp;prabhu-nity\u0101nanda&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">\u015br\u012b-advaita&nbsp;gad\u0101dhara&nbsp;\u015br\u012bv\u0101s\u0101di-gaura-bhakta-v\u1e5bnda&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">Hare&nbsp;K\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a&nbsp;Hare&nbsp;K\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a&nbsp;K\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a&nbsp;K\u1e5b\u1e63\u1e47a&nbsp;Hare&nbsp;Hare&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">Hare R\u0101ma Hare R\u0101ma&nbsp;R\u0101ma&nbsp;R\u0101ma&nbsp;Hare Hare&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\"><strong>HH Bhanu Swami&nbsp;Maharaj :&nbsp;<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">So previously we discussed how as one&nbsp;practices&nbsp;bhakti, one goes through a&nbsp;stage of&nbsp;anisthita&nbsp;or&nbsp;unsteadiness. But by following the process of bhakti, one reaches a&nbsp;stage of steadiness or&nbsp;nishtha.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img fetchpriority=\"high\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"901\" height=\"507\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-256.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4602\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-256.png 901w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-256-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-256-768x432.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 901px) 100vw, 901px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">This of course is described also in&nbsp;Srimad&nbsp;Bhagavatam in the first&nbsp;canto,&nbsp;we have verses like this.&nbsp;So&nbsp;in this&nbsp;particular verse,&nbsp;it says that Krishna within the heart destroys all&nbsp;anarthas&nbsp;or&nbsp;abhadrani&nbsp;[Laughs].&nbsp;Of course&nbsp;they&#8217;re not all destroyed but one reaches a&nbsp;stage which we call,&nbsp;here&nbsp;is called&nbsp;naishtiki&nbsp;bhakti or this is what we call&nbsp;nishtha.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"882\" height=\"543\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-262.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4609\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-262.png 882w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-262-300x185.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-262-768x473.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 882px) 100vw, 882px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">However not&nbsp;all of&nbsp;the&nbsp;anarthas&nbsp; are destroyed, sufficiently they are destroyed so one can practice steadily.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"879\" height=\"546\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-245.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4592\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-245.png 879w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-245-300x186.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-245-768x477.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 879px) 100vw, 879px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">So\u00a0Vishwanath\u00a0Chakravarti describes a\u00a0stage in terms of\u00a0absence\u00a0of six qualities.\u00a0So\u00a0the first is\u00a0absence\u00a0of\u00a0laya\u00a0or sleep.\u00a0So\u00a0when one is practicing bhakti or hearing and chanting\u00a0etc, one doesn&#8217;t fall asleep.\u00a0So\u00a0if there&#8217;s\u00a0absence\u00a0of\u00a0this,\u00a0then this is a sign of\u00a0nishtha.\u00a0\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"801\" height=\"573\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-191.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4538\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-191.png 801w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-191-300x215.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-191-768x549.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 801px) 100vw, 801px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">There&#8217;s&nbsp;an absence of giving material interpretations to scripture and the name.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"840\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-201.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4548\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-201.png 840w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-201-300x201.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-201-768x516.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 840px) 100vw, 840px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">There is an absence of indifference.&nbsp;So&nbsp;one may not be sleepy, one may not be distracted in mind, still one is not very eager to chant and hear.&nbsp;So&nbsp;at the&nbsp;stage of&nbsp;nishtha&nbsp;then one is very enthusiastic to do all the&nbsp;different aspects&nbsp;of bhakti.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"901\" height=\"561\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-205.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4552\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-205.png 901w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-205-300x187.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-205-768x478.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 901px) 100vw, 901px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p>There&#8217;s&nbsp;absence&nbsp;of&nbsp;kashaya&nbsp;which means sinful habits, anger, greed, pride etc.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"901\" height=\"567\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-241.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4588\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-241.png 901w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-241-300x189.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-241-768x483.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 901px) 100vw, 901px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p>And there&#8217;s&nbsp;absence&nbsp;of material taste.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"894\" height=\"570\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-230.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4577\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-230.png 894w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-230-300x191.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-230-768x490.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 894px) 100vw, 894px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">So&nbsp;if these things are&nbsp;absent,&nbsp;then these are signs of being at the&nbsp;stage of&nbsp;nishtha. This does not mean that all&nbsp;anarthas&nbsp;are gone, but they&nbsp;don&#8217;t&nbsp;cause problems for execution of bhakti.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"828\" height=\"372\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-264.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4611\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-264.png 828w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-264-300x135.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-264-768x345.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 828px) 100vw, 828px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">So&nbsp;in the beginning&nbsp;stages of bhakti,&nbsp;there&#8217;s&nbsp;a little bhakti and a lot of&nbsp;anarthas&nbsp;&nbsp;and therefore there is unsteadiness.&nbsp;And as one&nbsp;hears and chants&nbsp;and performs other actions of bhakti, the bhakti increases and&nbsp;anarthas&nbsp;&nbsp;begin to decrease. And when the bhakti becomes a little bit stronger than the&nbsp;anarthas, then you can practice bhakti steadily.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"901\" height=\"574\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-210.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4557\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-210.png 901w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-210-300x191.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-210-768x489.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 901px) 100vw, 901px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">Okay, so of course after this&nbsp;stage, when we go to Ruchi and Asakti and&nbsp;into&nbsp;Bhava, more&nbsp;anarthas&nbsp;are removed.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"822\" height=\"348\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-266.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4613\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-266.png 822w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-266-300x127.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-266-768x325.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 822px) 100vw, 822px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">So&nbsp;the last traces of&nbsp;anarthas&nbsp;are removed in Bhava, that makes Prema a perfect&nbsp;state with no&nbsp;anarthas.&nbsp;So&nbsp;throughout the process of bhakti, this&nbsp;anartha&nbsp;nivrutti&nbsp;is taking place. And gradually the bhakti increases.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"798\" height=\"438\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-267.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4614\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-267.png 798w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-267-300x165.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-267-768x422.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 798px) 100vw, 798px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">Vishwanath&nbsp;Chakravarti describes two types of&nbsp;steadiness.&nbsp;You can be steady in bodily activities in&nbsp;bhakti, with&nbsp;the words&nbsp;or with the mind. If we reach this steadiness in&nbsp;bhakti&nbsp;stage of&nbsp;nishtha, we can also perceive steadiness in others.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"831\" height=\"540\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-198.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4545\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-198.png 831w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-198-300x195.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-198-768x499.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 831px) 100vw, 831px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">And this fits in with the description of&nbsp;the Madhyama&nbsp;Adhikari.&nbsp;However, steadiness in those qualities is not always a sign of steadiness in bhakti. The Madhyama Adhikari distinguishes devotees from non-devotees.&nbsp;He also distinguishes&nbsp;the Kanistha&nbsp;from Madhyama and Uttama.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"870\" height=\"414\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-187.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4534\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-187.png 870w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-187-300x143.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-187-768x365.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 870px) 100vw, 870px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">Okay, so one can have steadiness in qualities such as humility, respect, friendliness, mercy etc.\u00a0However\u00a0steadiness in those qualities is not always\u00a0a sign of steadiness in bhakti. And the reason is\u00a0that,\u00a0one can have steadiness in certain qualities which are\u00a0sattvic\u00a0qualities.\u00a0\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"864\" height=\"372\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-219.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4566\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-219.png 864w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-219-300x129.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-219-768x331.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 864px) 100vw, 864px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">&nbsp;<br><strong>Translator&nbsp;Devotee :&nbsp;<\/strong>Which&nbsp;aren\u2019t&nbsp;or are ?&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br><strong>HH Bhanu Swami&nbsp;Maharaj&nbsp;:&nbsp;<\/strong>Sattvic qualities, hmm.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br><strong>Translator&nbsp;Devotee :&nbsp;<\/strong>They are or&nbsp;they are&nbsp;not ?&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br><strong>HH Bhanu Swami&nbsp;Maharaj&nbsp;:&nbsp;<\/strong>Yes, we see people, many brahmanas are steady in many nice qualities, sattvic qualities.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\"><strong>Translator&nbsp;Devotee:<\/strong>&nbsp;Okay,&nbsp;yeah.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\"><strong>HH Bhanu Swami&nbsp;Maharaj:&nbsp;<\/strong>But they may not have any bhakti at all [Laughs].&nbsp;So&nbsp;when we talk about qualities in bhakti, those are spiritual qualities, they will naturally develop as the devotee progresses.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"825\" height=\"585\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-212.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4559\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-212.png 825w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-212-300x213.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-212-768x545.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 825px) 100vw, 825px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">So&nbsp;from&nbsp;nishtha, when the bhakti becomes stronger and the&nbsp;anarthas&nbsp;becomes less, we get&nbsp;ruchi.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"744\" height=\"528\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-246.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4593\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-246.png 744w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-246-300x213.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 744px) 100vw, 744px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">From&nbsp;nishtha, when the bhakti becomes stronger and the&nbsp;anarthas&nbsp;becomes less, we get&nbsp;ruchi.&nbsp;So&nbsp;one has a great taste for the activities of bhakti, such as hearing and chanting.&nbsp;The&nbsp;anarthas&nbsp;are much less, so one has less interest in material enjoyment.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"846\" height=\"453\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-206.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4553\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-206.png 846w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-206-300x161.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-206-768x411.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 846px) 100vw, 846px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">So&nbsp;one does not experience fatigue or&nbsp;tiredness,&nbsp;when&nbsp;one does&nbsp;hearing&nbsp;and chanting. And when we have that&nbsp;ruchi, one becomes more addicted or more attracted to the activities of bhakti.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"870\" height=\"300\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-188.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4535\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-188.png 870w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-188-300x103.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-188-768x265.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 870px) 100vw, 870px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">&nbsp;<br>So in the material world, if we have jaundice, the effect of the liver, we cannot taste sugar. Of course we can taste it, but it tastes bitter, not&nbsp;sweet&nbsp;[Laughs].&nbsp;So similarly, we do the activities of bhakti,&nbsp;hearing&nbsp;and chanting, but&nbsp;they&#8217;re&nbsp;difficult to do,&nbsp;because&nbsp;they&#8217;re&nbsp;not so enjoyable.&nbsp;So&nbsp;the cure for jaundice is sugar,&nbsp;even though it&nbsp;doesn\u2019t&nbsp;taste&nbsp;nice [Laughs].&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"780\" height=\"504\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-213.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4560\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-213.png 780w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-213-300x194.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-213-768x496.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 780px) 100vw, 780px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">So&nbsp;if we are diseased with our intelligence,&nbsp;we will&nbsp;understand&nbsp;we&nbsp;should take the sugar even though it&nbsp;doesn\u2019t&nbsp;taste good and then gradually we develop taste, we get cured and we can taste the sweetness.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"894\" height=\"477\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-252.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4599\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-252.png 894w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-252-300x160.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-252-768x410.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 894px) 100vw, 894px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">So&nbsp;in the same way, gradually by performing hearing and chanting, we get cured of material disease, and we begin to taste and relish hearing and chanting.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"901\" height=\"573\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-253.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4600\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-253.png 901w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-253-300x191.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-253-768x488.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 901px) 100vw, 901px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">There are two types of&nbsp;ruchi. One may be attracted&nbsp;and have a taste for kirtan, if&nbsp;nice music is there, nice tunes are&nbsp;there&nbsp;[Laughs].&nbsp;So&nbsp;this is one type of&nbsp;ruchi, but&nbsp;it&#8217;s&nbsp;inferior.&nbsp;Real&nbsp;ruchi&nbsp;doesn&#8217;t&nbsp;depend on material conditions.&nbsp;So&nbsp;the devotee will be attracted to kirtan, whether it is musical or not musical&nbsp;[Laughs].&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"843\" height=\"543\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-216.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4563\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-216.png 843w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-216-300x193.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-216-768x495.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 843px) 100vw, 843px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">At the&nbsp;stage of&nbsp;ruchi, that devotee will lament his&nbsp;previous&nbsp;condition, where he had&nbsp;anarthas.&nbsp;He&#8217;s&nbsp;always hearing and chanting in association with the devotees. Because he has great attraction for devotional activities, he becomes very disgusted with material activities.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"837\" height=\"576\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-217.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4564\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-217.png 837w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-217-300x206.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-217-768x529.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 837px) 100vw, 837px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">He may retire to the holy&nbsp;dham&nbsp;to perform his bhakti [Laughs].&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"774\" height=\"495\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-242.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4589\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-242.png 774w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-242-300x192.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-242-768x491.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 774px) 100vw, 774px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">So&nbsp;as the bhakti increases and the&nbsp;anarthas&nbsp; decrease, one comes to the&nbsp;stage of&nbsp;asakti&nbsp;or attachment.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"828\" height=\"531\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-234.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4581\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-234.png 828w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-234-300x192.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-234-768x493.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 828px) 100vw, 828px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">In&nbsp;Nectar of devotion, bhakti was described as a little plant, and it grows leaves. The plant grows&nbsp;bigger, and&nbsp;then flower buds begin to appear.&nbsp;So, the&nbsp;stage of&nbsp;asakti&nbsp;is compared to the buds on the bhakti plant.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"873\" height=\"453\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-195.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4542\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-195.png 873w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-195-300x156.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-195-768x399.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 873px) 100vw, 873px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">So&nbsp;at the&nbsp;stage of&nbsp;ruchi, one is attracted to&nbsp;the hearing&nbsp;and chanting.&nbsp;And if one comes to&nbsp;asakti, one is attracted to Krishna, who is the object of your hearing and chanting.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"849\" height=\"420\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-268.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4615\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-268.png 849w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-268-300x148.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-268-768x380.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 849px) 100vw, 849px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">Near\u00a0Ruchi\u00a0stage, you still\u00a0have to\u00a0make efforts to withdraw the mind from material objects, etc.\u00a0At the\u00a0stage of Asakti, no effort is\u00a0required. One very spontaneously is attracted to Krishna.\u00a0\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"873\" height=\"399\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-190.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4537\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-190.png 873w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-190-300x137.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-190-768x351.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 873px) 100vw, 873px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">At this&nbsp;stage, Krishna almost appears [Laughs]. A reflection of Krishna appears in the heart.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"840\" height=\"465\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-199.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4546\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-199.png 840w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-199-300x166.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-199-768x425.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 840px) 100vw, 840px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">What is the characteristic of this devotee?\u00a0He\u00a0is attracted to devotees.\u00a0He is attracted to hearing from devotees.\u00a0He sees everything in relation to\u00a0and\u00a0how to\u00a0attain\u00a0Krishna. He disregards the opinions of others.\u00a0So\u00a0he may appear to be very strange in his behavior.\u00a0But he\u00a0doesn&#8217;t\u00a0mind what others say.\u00a0\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"837\" height=\"585\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-214.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4561\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-214.png 837w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-214-300x210.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-214-768x537.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 837px) 100vw, 837px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">He wants just to get&nbsp;closer and closer&nbsp;to Krishna [Laughs]. But at the end of Asakti, actually the&nbsp;anarthas&nbsp;due to karma are all gone.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"849\" height=\"588\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-261.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4608\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-261.png 849w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-261-300x208.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-261-768x532.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 849px) 100vw, 849px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">&nbsp;<br>So, from&nbsp;asakti&nbsp;one goes to the&nbsp;stage of Bhava.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"825\" height=\"540\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-238.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4585\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-238.png 825w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-238-300x196.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-238-768x503.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 825px) 100vw, 825px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">Asakti&nbsp;is like the bud of&nbsp;a flower.&nbsp;Bhava is like the flower blossoming&nbsp;[Laughs].&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"744\" height=\"588\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-247.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4594\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-247.png 744w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-247-300x237.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 744px) 100vw, 744px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">In the&nbsp;Bhava&nbsp;stage, there is the first appearance of Krishna.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"783\" height=\"582\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-259.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4606\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-259.png 783w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-259-300x223.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-259-768x571.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 783px) 100vw, 783px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">So&nbsp;asakti&nbsp;was like a reflection of Krishna, here we&nbsp;actually have&nbsp;Krishna appearing.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"801\" height=\"579\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-223.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4570\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-223.png 801w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-223-300x217.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-223-768x555.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 801px) 100vw, 801px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">So&nbsp;with just a drop of Bhava, then ignorance is completely destroyed.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"747\" height=\"507\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-207.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4554\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-207.png 747w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-207-300x204.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 747px) 100vw, 747px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">Previously,&nbsp;we&nbsp;described how suffering was all from&nbsp;karmas. Karmas came from&nbsp;actions. Actions came from all&nbsp;these raga,&nbsp;dvesha, etc.&nbsp;ahankara and finally, the very cause of everything was ignorance or avidya.&nbsp;So&nbsp;in&nbsp;avidya,&nbsp;then the very root of all of our problems in the world is ignorance is destroyed in Bhava.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"627\" height=\"672\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-269.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4616\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-269.png 627w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-269-280x300.png 280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 627px) 100vw, 627px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">In Sadhana Bhakti, we get the beginning of destruction of karmas&nbsp;etc,&nbsp;kleshagni. And we get some manifestation of good spiritual qualities.&nbsp;In Bhava&nbsp;stage, the devotee is able to see Krishna.&nbsp;This is something which is very rare.&nbsp;The Jnani\u2019s and Yogis and&nbsp;Karmis&nbsp;cannot&nbsp;see Krishna&nbsp;at all, no matter what they do.&nbsp;Because the devotee sees Krishna and serves Krishna,&nbsp;the idea of liberation becomes very insignificant.&nbsp;so&nbsp;Jnanis&nbsp;and Yogis&nbsp;strive for liberation,&nbsp;that&#8217;s&nbsp;their goal&nbsp;but a devotee in Bhava&nbsp;rejects that completely.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"858\" height=\"447\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-211.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4558\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-211.png 858w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-211-300x156.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-211-768x400.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 858px) 100vw, 858px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">In Bhava&nbsp;stage, the devotee experiences bliss in a relationship&nbsp;with the Supreme Lord, and&nbsp;consequently&nbsp;liberation becomes useless&nbsp;[Laughs].&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"864\" height=\"615\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-248.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4595\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-248.png 864w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-248-300x214.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-248-768x547.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 864px) 100vw, 864px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">In this&nbsp;stage, Bhava is&nbsp;very attractive&nbsp;to Krishna.&nbsp;So&nbsp;Krishna appears before the devotee. And the devotee becomes more attracted to Krishna.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"876\" height=\"465\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-200.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4547\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-200.png 876w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-200-300x159.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-200-768x408.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 876px) 100vw, 876px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">So&nbsp;at this&nbsp;stage, because&nbsp;he&#8217;s&nbsp;able to see Krishna, he must have spiritual eyes.&nbsp;So actually, he&nbsp;develops a spiritual&nbsp;body&nbsp;and all spiritual senses also develop, so he can see, smell, hear, touch and taste.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"882\" height=\"441\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-218.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4565\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-218.png 882w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-218-300x150.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-218-768x384.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 882px) 100vw, 882px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">Of course, we should not think that&nbsp;somehow&nbsp;he creates a body, because if&nbsp;it&#8217;s&nbsp;a spiritual body, it cannot be created,&nbsp;it&#8217;s&nbsp;eternal&nbsp;[Laughs].&nbsp;So&nbsp;eternal&nbsp;spiritual body manifests in the&nbsp;Jiva&nbsp;at this point.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"901\" height=\"663\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-220.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4567\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-220.png 901w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-220-300x221.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-220-768x565.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 901px) 100vw, 901px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">So&nbsp;because he is&nbsp;operating&nbsp;spiritual&nbsp;body, his material body is almost lifeless. Spiritual qualities manifest strongly. He becomes very possessive of Krishna.&nbsp;Because&nbsp;he&#8217;s&nbsp;absorbed&nbsp;in&nbsp;Krishna, for a materialist, he looks like he is insane.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"849\" height=\"444\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-221.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4568\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-221.png 849w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-221-300x157.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-221-768x402.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 849px) 100vw, 849px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">If one practices&nbsp;Vaidhi&nbsp;Sadhana Bhakti, one can develop Bhava. But&nbsp;it&#8217;s&nbsp;a little weak and not spontaneous.&nbsp;The reason for this&nbsp;is,&nbsp;one sees the Lord as a powerful figure.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"834\" height=\"582\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-249.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4596\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-249.png 834w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-249-300x209.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-249-768x536.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 834px) 100vw, 834px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">If one performs&nbsp;Raghanuga&nbsp;Sadhana Bhakti, then that Bhava is&nbsp;very strong&nbsp;and spontaneous. One does not see Krishna as a powerful Lord, but simply as a friend.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"831\" height=\"540\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-244.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4591\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-244.png 831w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-244-300x195.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-244-768x499.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 831px) 100vw, 831px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">So, from&nbsp;Vaidhi&nbsp;Sadhana, you can get to Bhava and Prema, but your realization of Krishna is a little different [Laughs].&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"825\" height=\"465\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-270.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4617\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-270.png 825w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-270-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-270-768x433.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 825px) 100vw, 825px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">In relation to Krishna, then at the&nbsp;Bhava&nbsp;stage, one can have various tastes.&nbsp;They can be Santa, or Dasya, Sakhya, Vatsalya, Madhurya.&nbsp;So&nbsp;this acting as a servant is compared to&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>to&nbsp;a&nbsp;grape&nbsp;juice.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"901\" height=\"604\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-235.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4582\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-235.png 901w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-235-300x201.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-235-768x515.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 901px) 100vw, 901px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">Acting as a friend is like sugar cane juice.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"765\" height=\"546\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-250.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4597\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-250.png 765w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-250-300x214.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 765px) 100vw, 765px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">If one has Vatsalya, it is like jackfruit juice [Laughs].&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"735\" height=\"549\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-224.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4571\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-224.png 735w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-224-300x224.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 735px) 100vw, 735px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\"><strong>Devotee :&nbsp;<\/strong>Oh, I wonder what taste that is.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\"><strong>HH Bhanu Swami&nbsp;Maharaj :&nbsp;<\/strong>[Laughs]&nbsp;And if you have a taste for Madhurya&nbsp;&#8211; conjugal rasa, it is like mango juice&nbsp;[Laughs].&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"813\" height=\"573\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-257.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4604\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-257.png 813w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-257-300x211.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-257-768x541.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 813px) 100vw, 813px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">So,&nbsp;Bhava&nbsp;actually means&nbsp;Sthayi&nbsp;Bhava.&nbsp;That&#8217;s&nbsp;this relationship,&nbsp;Santa, Dasya, Sakya, Vatsalya, Madhurya. This is combined with these other elements,&nbsp;Vibhava&nbsp;,&nbsp;Sattvika&nbsp;Bhava&nbsp;,&nbsp;Anubhava, and&nbsp;Vyabhacari&nbsp;Bhava&nbsp;.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"642\" height=\"411\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-189.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4536\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-189.png 642w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-189-300x192.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 642px) 100vw, 642px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">In order to&nbsp;have the&nbsp;Sthayi&nbsp;Baba,&nbsp;that\u2019s&nbsp;emotional&nbsp;relationship, you&nbsp;have to&nbsp;have a devotee&nbsp;and&nbsp;Krishna.&nbsp;Two people&nbsp;have to&nbsp;be&nbsp;there&nbsp;[Laughs].&nbsp;That&#8217;s&nbsp;the Vibhava&nbsp;[Laughs].&nbsp;So, once we have the devotee&nbsp;and&nbsp;Krishna, and we have the&nbsp;Sthayi&nbsp;Bhava&nbsp;established, then we will&nbsp;have ecstatic symptoms called&nbsp;Sattvika&nbsp;Bhavas.&nbsp;The devotee will manifest Anu&nbsp;bhavas,&nbsp;these are various activities or&nbsp;service.&nbsp;And there will be some minor emotions like doubt or fear&nbsp;etc, jealously, that\u2019s temporary manifestation that is called&nbsp;Vyabhacari&nbsp;bhava&nbsp; and&nbsp;these all&nbsp;combine together, and that produces rasa.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"843\" height=\"648\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-231.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4578\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-231.png 843w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-231-300x231.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-231-768x590.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 843px) 100vw, 843px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">And that rasa is expressed in Santa, Dasya, Sakhya, Vatsalya, or Madhurya.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"801\" height=\"534\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-255.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4603\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-255.png 801w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-255-300x200.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-255-768x512.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 801px) 100vw, 801px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">So&nbsp;we have&nbsp;the five&nbsp;primary rasas.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"840\" height=\"510\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-215.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4562\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-215.png 840w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-215-300x182.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-215-768x466.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 840px) 100vw, 840px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">And depending on them, we have some secondary rasas.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"774\" height=\"558\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-227.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4574\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-227.png 774w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-227-300x216.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-227-768x554.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 774px) 100vw, 774px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">So&nbsp;the&nbsp;Lord has&nbsp;many forms, but they are all rasas. But Krishna is the personification of&nbsp;rasa&nbsp;[Laughs], because&nbsp;he manifests all rasas fully.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"828\" height=\"525\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-263.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4610\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-263.png 828w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-263-300x190.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-263-768x487.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 828px) 100vw, 828px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">So,&nbsp;Bhava&nbsp;is like the first experience of rasa, not fully developed.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"831\" height=\"447\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-203.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4550\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-203.png 831w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-203-300x161.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-203-768x413.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 831px) 100vw, 831px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p>So then, that&nbsp;Bhava&nbsp;turns into Prema.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"807\" height=\"567\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-243.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4590\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-243.png 807w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-243-300x211.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-243-768x540.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 807px) 100vw, 807px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">And Prema is like the fruit that manifests after the flower.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"747\" height=\"591\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-232.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4579\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-232.png 747w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-232-300x237.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 747px) 100vw, 747px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">But when that fruit develops, the flowers&nbsp;remain, the buds&nbsp;remain, the leaves&nbsp;remain, everything&nbsp;remains&nbsp;[Laughs].&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"858\" height=\"606\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-258.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4605\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-258.png 858w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-258-300x212.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-258-768x542.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 858px) 100vw, 858px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">Okay, so in that&nbsp;state of Prema, there is not just bliss,&nbsp;as&nbsp;in&nbsp;Bhava&nbsp;there is bliss. This is concentrated bliss, intense bliss. Krishna is attracted to any type of bhakti, but he is most attracted to Prema bhakti.&nbsp;So, in Bhava&nbsp;stage, there is possessiveness of Krishna. In Prema, there is intense possessiveness of Krishna.&nbsp;And there is a greed for Krishna, which will overcome any obstacle. If Krishna appears for a moment, then&nbsp;the greed&nbsp;increases.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"867\" height=\"645\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-260.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4607\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-260.png 867w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-260-300x223.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-260-768x571.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 867px) 100vw, 867px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">One has a longing for Krishna, and longing for Krishna to bestow bliss.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"846\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-236.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4583\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-236.png 846w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-236-300x200.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-236-768x512.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 846px) 100vw, 846px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">So, in Prema, Krishna appears in all the senses. He reveals his form to the eyes. He reveals his fragrance to the&nbsp;nose.&nbsp;He reveals his voice to the ear.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"828\" height=\"516\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-222.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4569\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-222.png 828w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-222-300x187.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-222-768x479.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 828px) 100vw, 828px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">Then he touches the devotee [Laughs]. And he reveals taste to those in Madhurya Rasa.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"864\" height=\"552\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-254.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4601\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-254.png 864w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-254-300x192.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-254-768x491.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 864px) 100vw, 864px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">Then he reveals his beauty, fragrance, sound, touch, taste, everything simultaneously to all the senses at once. And then he bestows his Kripa Shakti, Shakti of Mercy, so the devotee can experience everything simultaneously.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"789\" height=\"405\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-204.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4551\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-204.png 789w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-204-300x154.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-204-768x394.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 789px) 100vw, 789px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">So, in Prema, there are two phases, meeting and separation. When Krishna meets the devotee, then the devotee experiences the highest bliss.&nbsp;&nbsp;And when Krishna separates himself from the devotee, the devotee feels the greatest pain.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"789\" height=\"582\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-237.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4584\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-237.png 789w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-237-300x221.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-237-768x567.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 789px) 100vw, 789px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">So, in the material world, the devotee has his body, but simultaneously he is experiencing Krishna in his spiritual body.\u00a0And the devotee is not really aware of his material body at all.\u00a0So, finally, he gives up the material body completely and enters into the spiritual world with his spiritual body.\u00a0\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"831\" height=\"450\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-233.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4580\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-233.png 831w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-233-300x162.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-233-768x416.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 831px) 100vw, 831px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">&nbsp;<br>So, the&nbsp;different&nbsp;stages&nbsp;of bhakti have been described.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"603\" height=\"390\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-194.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4541\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-194.png 603w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-194-300x194.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 603px) 100vw, 603px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">Okay [Laughs], yes.&nbsp;So&nbsp;we go through the&nbsp;different stages&nbsp;of&nbsp;bhakti, but the plant begins to develop from the&nbsp;seed,&nbsp;it develops leaves.&nbsp;Finally, we get a bud, the bud turns into a flower, the&nbsp;flower turns into fruit. So, bhakti grows within the&nbsp;Jiva, just like a plant.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"879\" height=\"630\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-228.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4575\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-228.png 879w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-228-300x215.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-228-768x550.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 879px) 100vw, 879px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">When one gets to&nbsp;prema, in the spiritual world, there&nbsp;is&nbsp;further&nbsp;stages that manifest.&nbsp;When&nbsp;prema&nbsp;becomes&nbsp;condensed or&nbsp;thick and melts the heart,&nbsp;it&#8217;s&nbsp;called&nbsp;sneha.&nbsp;When there&nbsp;is&nbsp;some contrary feelings like anger and pride that is called Maan.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"837\" height=\"546\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-239.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4586\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-239.png 837w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-239-300x196.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-239-768x501.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 837px) 100vw, 837px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">When there is great&nbsp;affection,&nbsp;so&nbsp;there is no longer any sense of respect,&nbsp;that\u2019s&nbsp;called&nbsp;pranaya. That is quite prominent in Sakhya rasa where their&nbsp;friends they&nbsp;don\u2019t&nbsp;have any respect [Laughs]. When&nbsp;sneha&nbsp;turns sorrow into happiness when Krishna appears, it is called raga.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"843\" height=\"441\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-225.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4572\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-225.png 843w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-225-300x157.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-225-768x402.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 843px) 100vw, 843px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">Then&nbsp;Anuraga, which appears in&nbsp;Madhurya&nbsp;rasa, is even more intense.&nbsp;And that love, every time one experiences, it&nbsp;becomes&nbsp;newer and newer. The highest type of&nbsp;prema&nbsp;is maha&nbsp;bhava.&nbsp;And this is only experienced by&nbsp;the&nbsp;Gopis in Vrindavan.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"846\" height=\"498\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-229.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4576\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-229.png 846w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-229-300x177.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-229-768x452.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 846px) 100vw, 846px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">Okay&nbsp;so we have various&nbsp;stages of intensity [Laughs].&nbsp;So&nbsp;this&nbsp;material&nbsp;human&nbsp;body cannot experience all of this nicely. So therefore, only when you go to the spiritual world do you get these later&nbsp;stages.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"798\" height=\"456\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-208.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4555\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-208.png 798w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-208-300x171.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-208-768x439.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 798px) 100vw, 798px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">So&nbsp;at the end of this work,&nbsp;Vishwananth&nbsp;Chakravarti analyzes possessiveness.&nbsp;But in the material world, possessiveness is&nbsp;a bad quality. I and&nbsp;mine&nbsp;as a result of&nbsp;ahankara.&nbsp;This produces bondage in the material world.&nbsp;So&nbsp;Yogis and&nbsp;Jnanis want to destroy ahankara to get liberation.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"777\" height=\"555\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-197.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4544\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-197.png 777w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-197-300x214.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-197-768x549.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 777px) 100vw, 777px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">However, apart from that material ahankara, there is a spiritual ahankara in the&nbsp;Jiva.&nbsp;So&nbsp;there is a&nbsp;spirtiual&nbsp;\u2018I\u2019.&nbsp;So&nbsp;we say&nbsp;I&#8217;m&nbsp;the servant of Krishna. And the&nbsp;devotee has&nbsp;possessiveness of Krishna&nbsp;[Laughs]. So that I and mine in spiritual life is a positive feature, it produces&nbsp;prema.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"756\" height=\"366\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-271.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4618\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-271.png 756w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-271-300x145.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 756px) 100vw, 756px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">So&nbsp;as we go through the&nbsp;different stages&nbsp;from sraddha to&nbsp;prema, then gradually the material possessiveness and ahankara get&nbsp;weaker and weaker and weaker&nbsp;and the identification&nbsp;I&#8217;m&nbsp;the servant of Krishna gets&nbsp;stronger and stronger and stronger.&nbsp;So&nbsp;when we begin bhakti with sraddha,&nbsp;etc, attachment to matter and ahankara is&nbsp;very strong. But as we go into&nbsp;bhajana&nbsp;kriya and&nbsp;anartha&nbsp;nivrutti, gradually attraction to matter and ahankara&nbsp;become&nbsp;weaker and weaker. And gradually the attraction to Krishna, possessiveness of Krishna becomes&nbsp;stronger and stronger.&nbsp;So&nbsp;we reach this&nbsp;stage of&nbsp;Bhava&nbsp;,&nbsp;the identification with the material body,&nbsp;etc, is very&nbsp;very&nbsp;slight and attraction to Krishna is very&nbsp;very&nbsp;strong.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"901\" height=\"651\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-251.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4598\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-251.png 901w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-251-300x217.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-251-768x555.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 901px) 100vw, 901px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">And we get to&nbsp;prema, then nothing to do with the material world at all, and the attraction and possessiveness of Krishna is very intense.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"846\" height=\"618\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-196.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4543\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-196.png 846w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-196-300x219.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-196-768x561.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 846px) 100vw, 846px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p>And similarly, we can trace meditation.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"552\" height=\"642\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-240.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4587\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-240.png 552w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-240-258x300.png 258w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 552px) 100vw, 552px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">Meditation, of course, on material things is strong in the beginning and becomes&nbsp;weaker and weaker, and meditation on Krishna is weak in the beginning and it becomes&nbsp;stronger and stronger&nbsp;as we develop.&nbsp;So&nbsp;if one is at the&nbsp;stage of&nbsp;asakti, the meditation is very deep. And then in&nbsp;Bhava&nbsp;stage, Krishna appears internally.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"831\" height=\"546\" src=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-209.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-4556\" srcset=\"https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-209.png 831w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-209-300x197.png 300w, https:\/\/bhanuswamiarchives.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2026\/01\/image-209-768x505.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 831px) 100vw, 831px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\"><strong>Devotee :&nbsp;<\/strong>Internally or eternally?&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br><strong>HH Bhanu Swami&nbsp;Maharaj :<\/strong>&nbsp;Internally. And then in&nbsp;prema, Krishna directly appears in front of you.&nbsp;Yeah, okay, fine, that&#8217;s&nbsp;it&nbsp;[Laughs].&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">Hare Krishna.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\">&nbsp;<br><strong>Q &amp; A:<\/strong>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\"><strong>1.)&nbsp;Thank you for the very wonderful and&nbsp;very sweet&nbsp;class. You mentioned that&nbsp;Bhava&nbsp;&nbsp;that&nbsp;can&nbsp;be originated&nbsp;from either sadhana bhakti or&nbsp;raganuga&nbsp;bhakti.&nbsp;So&nbsp;my question is, can a devotee directly go to raga naga bhakti without being in the sadhana bhakti?&nbsp;<\/strong>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br>Raganuga is&nbsp;sadhana.&nbsp;So&nbsp;raganuga&nbsp;and&nbsp;vaidhi&nbsp;are both sadhana. Of course, one could&nbsp;start with&nbsp;vaidhi&nbsp;sadhana and switch to&nbsp;raganuga&nbsp;sadhana. Or one could just continue&nbsp;vaidhi&nbsp;and have realization in&nbsp;Bhava&nbsp;and&nbsp;in&nbsp;prema&nbsp;with&nbsp;vaidhi.&nbsp;So&nbsp;it is possible to do&nbsp;raganuga&nbsp;from the beginning of sadhana.&nbsp;So&nbsp;we have, for instance, the&nbsp;Vallabha sampradaya. The whole&nbsp;[Laughs]&nbsp;sadhana&nbsp;is also&nbsp;raganuga&nbsp;from the beginning.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\"><strong>2.)&nbsp;I understand&nbsp;Maharaj. Thank you so much. Another question is, you mentioned that in the&nbsp;stage of&nbsp;prema, when&nbsp;devotee&nbsp;has the spiritual body, then again there are many&nbsp;stages and one of them was, I think, is&nbsp;anurag.&nbsp;And you mentioned that in that&nbsp;stage,&nbsp;devotee&nbsp;may think of giving up his body.&nbsp;So&nbsp;in a spiritual body, how&nbsp;can a devotee can&nbsp;think of giving up his body?&nbsp;<\/strong>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br>Because their bodies are fully spiritual, they can never give up their bodies. But they have this feeling that&nbsp;they&#8217;re&nbsp;ready to sacrifice themselves for Krishna.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br><strong>Devotee :&nbsp;<\/strong>I understand&nbsp;Maharaj. Thank you so much.&nbsp;This lecture is&nbsp;based on Madhurya Kadambini or&nbsp;different&nbsp;book?&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\"><strong>HH Bhanu Swami&nbsp;Maharaj :<\/strong>&nbsp;Madhurya Kadambini.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br><strong>Devotee :&nbsp;<\/strong>Thank you so much,&nbsp;Maharaj. Hare Krishna.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\"><strong>3.)&nbsp;Hare Krishna. Thank you for your wonderful session.&nbsp;Maybe first&nbsp;slide or second slide&nbsp;its&nbsp;mentioned somewhere that Krishna enters the heart of the devotee.&nbsp;What does that mean? Because already Krishna is in the heart as the&nbsp;Paramatma.&nbsp;So&nbsp;what exactly does it mean when&nbsp;Krishna enters the heart or enters the devotee?<\/strong>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br>Yeah of course&nbsp;Krishna&nbsp;[Not clear]&nbsp;but for the devotee&nbsp;[Not audible]&nbsp;more than&nbsp;Paramatma,&nbsp;Bhagavan functions.&nbsp;Paramatma&nbsp;is a neutral&nbsp;witness,&nbsp;Bhagavan reciprocates with the devotee.&nbsp;So&nbsp;therefore&nbsp;Krishna helps the devotee advance,&nbsp;he helps them destroy the&nbsp;anarthas.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br><strong>Devotee :&nbsp;<\/strong>Thank you very much.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br><strong>4.)&nbsp;Its&nbsp;related to the first question. In Bhava&nbsp;stage Krsna&nbsp;enters&nbsp;and the devotee can see Krishna in the heart. Is that correct?&nbsp;<\/strong>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br>Yeah, so at Nistha,&nbsp;he cannot really see Krishna. But Krishna destroys your&nbsp;anarthas&nbsp;[Laughs].&nbsp;So&nbsp;at Bhava&nbsp;stage then you can actually perceive Krishna with your spiritual eyes.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br><strong>Devotee :&nbsp;<\/strong>Thank you very much.&nbsp;Hare Krishna.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br><strong>5.) Hare Krishna Maharaj ji.&nbsp;When Krishna killed Kamsa and he settled in Mathura, to check the condition of the&nbsp;gopas&nbsp;and&nbsp;gopis&nbsp;in Vrindavan. He called Uddhava and sent Uddhava to Vrindavan by sending his message.&nbsp;There, Uddhava&nbsp;saw that all the&nbsp;Gopas&nbsp;and Gopis were in pain of separation from Krishna.&nbsp;So, Uddhav also felt the same pain and when he returned back, he was still in that pain.&nbsp;Even though Udhav was such a pure devotee and he was in a Prema&nbsp;Bhakti, why does it look like that separation is much higher than the satisfaction in meeting Lord Krishna?&nbsp;<\/strong>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br>So, in all relationships in the spiritual world, there are two aspects, meeting and separation. There are two parts of&nbsp;Prema.&nbsp;So, we usually look at the meeting as being very joyful. The separation looks painful. But that&#8217;s material&nbsp;perception.&nbsp;Because there can be no real pain in the spiritual world.&nbsp;So, that separation, that feeling of pain, is actually part of Prema itself.&nbsp;So, we can say&nbsp;it&#8217;s&nbsp;another aspect of bliss.&nbsp;So, it is said that in that separation, it looks like pain. There&#8217;s even greater bliss than the bliss of meeting. But that is&nbsp;very difficult&nbsp;to understand,&nbsp;unless you experience&nbsp;that&nbsp;Prema.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br><strong>Devotee :&nbsp;<\/strong>Thank&nbsp;you Maharaj ji. Hare Krishna.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br><strong>6.)&nbsp;<\/strong><strong>In one&nbsp;slide&nbsp;it was written that impurities are completely removed at Bhava&nbsp;stage,&nbsp;but we see that Bharath&nbsp;Maharaj&nbsp;fell down&nbsp;from Bhava&nbsp;stage. How can we understand this ?<\/strong>&nbsp;<br><strong><\/strong>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-justify has-text-align-justify\">So, all&nbsp;anarthas, due to Papa and Punya, etc., are finished by the end of Asakti. So, what&nbsp;remains&nbsp;in&nbsp;Bhava&nbsp;can be a trace of&nbsp;previous&nbsp;aparadh.&nbsp;So&nbsp;because Bharath had committed some offense in the&nbsp;previous&nbsp;life, the effect was felt in Bhava&nbsp;stage and then he forgot&nbsp;Vishnu and remembered a deer instead.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br><strong>Devotees :&nbsp;<\/strong>Hare Krishna. Thank you very much. HH Bhanu Swami Maharaj ji&nbsp;Jai !!!&nbsp;Srila&nbsp;Prabhupad&nbsp;ki&nbsp;Jai !!!&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Bhakti Lata&nbsp;\u2013&nbsp;3&nbsp;| HH Bhanu Swami Maharaj | ISKCON Japan |&nbsp;13 Nov 2025&nbsp; jaya&nbsp;r\u0101dh\u0101-m\u0101dhava&nbsp;ku\u00f1ja-vih\u0101r\u012b&nbsp;&nbsp; gop\u012bjana-vallabha&nbsp;giri-vara-dh\u0